cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the notion of avoidability of logical formulas. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a likely category as the paper involves combinatorial analysis of circular formulas. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the avoidability index of formulas is a measure of their complexity. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the analysis of circular formulas which are used in game theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not involve the design or analysis of algorithms or data structures.
